            <h2 id="sec4">Step 5: Microfluidic Chip</h2>
            <p>
                To setup your microfluidic chip, use the milled out control layer and flow layer.
            </p>
            <p> Use the PDMS to seal both layers using a vacuum chamber. This enables the chip to be sealed to
                prevent liquid from flowing out.
                Then add valves where needed to control the flow.
